                          <desc>The scribe occasionally has to complete a line of text on another line.
                            The challenge is addressed mainly through the selection of an appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined
                            with an appropriate script size. Where the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes the line of
                            text above the end of the line (e.g., f. 17r, etc.).
